		"description": "<p>At 9th level, you can draw upon your indomitable will to overcome pain, resist overwhelming forces, or retaliate when most warriors would be shirking back. You can use this feature to perform any of the following reactions:</p><ul><li>Reroll a failed saving throw. If you do so, you must use the new roll.</li><li>Reduce the damage you would take from a single source or attack by 2d8 + half your fighter level.</li><li>Make a single attack against a creature that has just completed an attack against you.</li></ul><p>You gain an additional use of this feature at 13th level and a third use starting at 17th leveI. You regain all spent uses of this feature whenever you finish a long rest.</p>",
